Scope PG_FORCE_DISABLE_INLINE to C so it does not break libc++.

PGlite's emscripten port defines PG_FORCE_DISABLE_INLINE (in
pg_config_os.h), which makes c.h do `#define inline` (empty).  That is
fine for PostgreSQL's C, but for C++ it turns libc++'s
`inline namespace __2 { ... }` into a plain namespace, so `std::__declval`,
`std::filesystem`, etc. resolve to the wrong scope and every C++
translation unit fails to compile.  Disabling `inline` is unnecessary for
C++ (emscripten's clang supports it), so restrict the override to C.

This blocks ANY C++ extension under PGlite, not just ProvSQL; the proper
home for the fix is upstream in electric-sql/postgres-pglite.

In src/include/c.h, change

    #ifdef PG_FORCE_DISABLE_INLINE

to

    #if defined(PG_FORCE_DISABLE_INLINE) && !defined(__cplusplus)

build-pglite.sh applies this idempotently with sed against the installed
server header (dist/include/postgresql/server/c.h).
